<![CDATA[ <p><a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/f1">Formula 1</a>&lsquo;s 2026 launch season is about to get into full swing, with <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/red-bull-racing">Red Bull</a> and <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/scuderia-alphatauri/">Racing Bulls</a> set to be first to reveal the look of their new cars on January 15.</p> <p>But don&rsquo;t expect to discover many design secrets when the covers are pulled off their cars &mdash; nor any of their rivals&rsquo; machines for that matter.</p> <p>F1 teams are always cagey about revealing too much too early, and they are set to be ultra-cautious this year when new regulations have forced each team to design their cars from a blank sheet of paper, meaning that any team could have come up with an ingenious concept that will propel them to the front of the grid.</p> <p>Any innovations are likely to be kept under wraps until testing &mdash; perhaps even until the first race of the season in Australia &mdash; so we&rsquo;ll initially be shown teams&rsquo; updated liveries on what are likely to be show cars, reflecting a generic car built to 2026 rules.</p> <h2><strong>2026 F1 car launch dates and livery reveals</strong></h2> <p><em>Click on any team to jump to more details</em></p> <table style="height: 288px;"> <thead> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <th style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;">Team</th> <th style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">Livery reveal date</th> <th style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">Car launch date</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#mclaren">McLaren</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">February 9</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#mercedes">Mercedes</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 22</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">February 2</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#redbull">Red Bull</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 15</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#ferrari">Ferrari</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 23</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">January 23</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#williams">Williams</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">February 3</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#racingbulls">Racing Bulls</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 15</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#aston">Aston Martin</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">February 9</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">February 9</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#haas">Haas</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 19</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#audi">Audi</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 20</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#alpine">Alpine&nbsp;</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">January 23</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 173.578px;"><a href="#cadillac">Cadillac</a></td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 160.406px;">February 8</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 137.547px;">TBC</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/haas-formula-1-team">Haas</a>, <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/sauber">Audi</a> and <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/mercedes-benz">Mercedes</a> will follow Red Bull with livery reveals but, as launch season continues, we&rsquo;re likely to start to see more unique details: <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/ferrari">Ferrari</a> may show a version of its new car on January 23, just ahead of the first testing session at Barcelona in late January, which will be held behind closed doors.</p> <p>Further launches are then planned, including new team Cadillac, which will reveal its livery during the half-time break at NFL&rsquo;s Super Bowl on February 8, a day ahead of Aston Martin and McLaren. Then there will be two public tests in Bahrain, where we should see all of this year&rsquo;s cars in full for the first time &mdash; although perhaps still missing one or two key components.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <h3><strong>2026 F1 pre-season testing</strong></h3> <p>The first running of the 2026 cars will take place behind closed doors at the Circuit de Barcelona&#8209;Catalunya from January 26-30.</p> <p>With the teams facing a seismic technical overhaul, the first shakedown will be kept entirely private: no television coverage, no journalists on site and no live social-media feed allowed.</p> <p>After that, two full public test sessions are scheduled in Bahrain, first on February 11-13 and then on February 18-20, with fans, media and broadcasters finally able to view the new machines ahead of the opening round.<a id="mclaren"></a></p> <table style="height: 96px;"> <thead> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <th style="height: 24px; width: 34.6562px;">Test</th> <th style="height: 24px; width: 333.25px;">Venue</th> <th style="height: 24px; width: 113.859px;">Dates</th> <th style="height: 24px; width: 206.75px;">Access</th> </tr> </thead> <tbody> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 34.6562px;">1</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 333.25px;">Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya (Spain)</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 113.859px;">January 26&ndash;30</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 206.75px;">Private / behind closed doors</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 34.6562px;">2</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 333.25px;">Bahrain International Circuit (Sakhir, Bahrain)</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 113.859px;">February 11&ndash;13</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 206.75px;">Public / open to media</td> </tr> <tr style="height: 24px;"> <td style="height: 24px; width: 34.6562px;">3</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 333.25px;">Bahrain International Circuit (Sakhir, Bahrain)</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 113.859px;">February 18&ndash;20</td> <td style="height: 24px; width: 206.75px;">Public / open to media</td> </tr> </tbody> </table> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h2><strong>F1 car launch dates 2026</strong></h2> <h3><strong>McLaren</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Reveal date: 9 February</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475480" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-scaled.jpg" alt="McLaren F1 hospitality unit" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/McLaren-F1-hospitality-unit-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>McLaren is set to reveal its livery two days before F1 testing in Bahrain and, as the reigning constructors&rsquo; champions, with the current world champion driver, the team won&rsquo;t need to do much to create headlines.</p> <p>At the factory, however, staff face a monumental task of building a car that can defend both titles with a customer engine deal. The introduction of sweeping new rules often favours factory teams, who are better placed to integrate power unit and chassis seamlessly.<a id="mercedes"></a></p> <h3></h3> <hr> <h3><strong>Mercedes</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 22<br> Car launch date: February 2</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475481" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-scaled.jpg" alt="F1 W17 graphic" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/F1-W17-graphic-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>The last time Formula 1 mandated an all-new powertrain, Mercedes was so dominant that it won eight constructors&rsquo; championships in uninterrupted succession, so it&rsquo;s not surprising that the team is the pre-season favourite.</p> <p>Of course, history is no guarantee of success, but paddock whisperings suggest that Mercedes&rsquo; engine dyno figures are fearsome, perhaps helped by a legal loophole that it has taken full advantage of.</p> <p>As the team saw in the ground effect era from 2022, having a leading engine can&rsquo;t save you if the chassis isn&rsquo;t up to it, but if it can take advantage of its factory programme to integrate power unit and chassis seamlessly in its new W17, the Silver Arrows may be unbeatable once more.<a id="redbull"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Red Bull</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 15</h4> <figure class="wp-caption"> <picture> <source type="image/webp" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-818x460.jpg.webp 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-660x371.jpg.webp 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-450x253.jpg.webp 450w"> <img height="450" width="800" alt="Red Bull F1 car under cover" class="" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-800x450.jpg" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Red-Bull-F1-car-under-cover-450x253.jpg 450w" loading="lazy"> </source></picture> <figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> 2026 Red Bull will be powered by in-house power-unit &mdash; with support from Ford <small>Red Bull</small> </figcaption> </figure> <p><a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/red-bull-racing">Red Bull</a>, alongside sister team <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/scuderia-alphatauri/">Racing Bulls</a>, is the first team to officially kick off the 2026 Formula 1 car launch season, with both teams set to reveal their livery at an event on January 15.</p> <p>The unveiling will take place at the Ford Racing Season Launch at the Michigan Central Station in Detroit.</p> <p>This is the first time both of Red Bull&rsquo;s teams will be unveiled together, and will mark the official introduction of the Ford Red Bull Powertrains unit, as Ford returns to Formula 1 after a 22-year absence.</p> <p>&ldquo;Since we announced our return to F1 with Red Bull, the team has been working night and day to get ready for 2026,&rdquo; said Mark Rushbrook, Ford Racing&rsquo;s global director. &ldquo;But this is about so much more than just the racing.</p> <p>&ldquo;It is about how we use our learnings from F1 to make our cars and trucks better for our customers. What we will learn together with Red Bull will define the technologies of the future and that is what excites me most about this relationship.&rdquo;<a id="ferrari"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Ferrari</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Car launch date: January 23</h4> <figure class="wp-caption"> <picture> <source type="image/webp" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-818x460.jpg.webp 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-678x381.jpg.webp 678w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-450x253.jpg.webp 450w"> <img height="450" width="800" alt="Ferrari F1 team principal Fred Vasseur in paddock" class="" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-800x450.jpg" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-678x381.jpg 678w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Ferrari-F1-team-principal-Fred-Vasseur-in-paddock-450x253.jpg 450w" loading="lazy"> </source></picture> <figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> 2026 marks the moment of truth for Fred Vasseur <small>Ferrari</small> </figcaption> </figure> <p>With an established team principal, perhaps the mightiest driver duo on the grid, and the vast resources of Maranello, Ferrari should have everything in place to challenge for the championship in 2026,</p> <p>Mind you, we thought the same in 2022. And 2025. The team rarely has the chance to escape its furrow of perennial underperformance before a new structure is imposed and the cycle of hope and despair begins again.</p> <p>Team principal Frederic Vasseur knows that failure won&rsquo;t be tolerated in 2026 &mdash; particularly after undermining rumours began to circulate during last year&rsquo;s disappointing season &mdash; so suggestions that Ferrari&rsquo;s power unit may be lacking in performance will be concerning for him, not to mention the long-suffering Charles Leclerc who&rsquo;s due a championship challenger, and Lewis Hamilton who deserves a final chance to shine.<a id="williams"></a></p> <h3></h3> <hr> <h3><strong>Williams</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: February 3</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475488" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-scaled.jpg" alt="Williams livery reveal image" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Williams-livery-reveal-image-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>We won&rsquo;t get the first glimpse of Williams&rsquo; new 2026 look until after the first testing session, in keeping for a team that&rsquo;s cloaked in intrigue for 2026.</p> <p>This is the season where Williams&rsquo; carefully-laid plans should start to come to fruition, after being bought by private investment firm Dorilton Capital, which appointed James Vowles to lead the team.</p> <p>He has spent the past two seasons on an extensive restructure, sacrificing immediate results to build the foundations for success, and securing the services of the dynamic Alex Albon and Carlos Sainz.</p> <p>If Williams is on track to meet its target of fighting for race wins in 2028, then we would expect to see it close to the front of the midfield in 2026. But given the team&rsquo;s progress so far, and its hotly-tipped Mercedes power-unit, don&rsquo;t write off its chances of the FW48 fighting at the front come the season-opening Australian Grand Prix.<a id="racingbulls"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Racing Bulls</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 15</h4> <figure class="wp-caption"> <picture> <source type="image/webp" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-818x460.jpg.webp 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-660x371.jpg.webp 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-450x253.jpg.webp 450w"> <img height="450" width="800" alt="Isack Hadjar and Yuki Tsunoda unveil 2025 Racing Bulls F1 car" class="" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-800x450.jpg" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Isack-Hadjar-and-Yuki-Tsunoda-unveil-2025-Racing-Bulls-F1-car-450x253.jpg 450w" loading="lazy"> </source></picture> <figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> Which drivers will be unveiling the Racing Bull in 2026? <small>Red Bull</small> </figcaption> </figure> <p><a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/scuderia-alphatauri/">Racing Bulls</a> will share the spotlight with <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/teams/red-bull-racing">Red Bull</a> Racing at a joint launch event, the first time both teams have unveiled their cars together.</p> <p>The team will also be powered by the Ford Red Bull Powertrains engine in 2026.</p> <p>The 2025 season saw Racing Bulls steadily close the gap to the frontrunners, with <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/drivers/isack-hadjar/">Isack Hadjar</a> even scoring a podium finish at <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/circuits/zandvoort">Zandvoort</a>.</p> <p>For 2026, the team is once again fielding a promising youngster in Arvid Lindblad, who replaces the Red Bull-bound Hadjar, alongside <a href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/database/drivers/liam-lawson/">Liam Lawson</a>.<a id="aston"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Aston Martin</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Car launch: February 9</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475492" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-scaled.jpg" alt="Overhead view of Aston Martin F1 car halo" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Overhead-view-of-Aston-Martin-F1-car-halo-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>Aston Martin will launch its 2026 car on February 9 after the behind-closed-doors Barcelona test, and it might be the most closely-watched one of the lot.</p> <p>No modern F1 designer can match Adrian Newey&rsquo;s track record when it comes to interpreting new regulations, so his first Aston Martin F1 car will be scrutinised carefully.</p> <p>In reality, that&rsquo;s only likely to happen during Bahrain testing. If the past is any guide, Aston won&rsquo;t reveal the fine details at its launch event, although the ultimate decision will fall to Newey as the new team boss.<a id="haas"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Haas</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 19</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475493" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-scaled.jpg" alt="Haas logo on F1 pit light" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Haas-logo-on-F1-pit-light-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>Haas initially planned to release the first images of its 2026 livery on January 23, along with Ferrari and Alpine, but has brought the date forward &ldquo;to avoid traffic&rdquo;.</p> <p>Ahead of testing, the team will be attempting to secure its new identity in the minds of fans; Haas&rsquo;s tie-up with Toyota Gazoo Racing now extends to its official name which becomes TGR Haas F1 Team.</p> <p>However, another partnership looks to be more crucial to Haas&rsquo;s hopes of continuing its ascent up the grid: the success of engine supplier Ferrari is likely to make or break the team&rsquo;s 2026 season.<a id="audi"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Audi</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 20</h4> <h3><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1470895" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-scaled.jpg" alt="Audi F1 2026 car livery with ring background" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/Audi-F1-2026-car-livery-with-ring-background-818x460.jpg 818w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></h3> <p>Audi&rsquo;s takeover of Sauber is complete, and with comes a rebrand, which began last year with the reveal of a &ldquo;concept livery&rdquo;.</p> <p>Fans will be enthused to know that the team now plans a second &ldquo;official&rdquo; livery reveal on January 20 in Berlin.</p> <p>The team will be officially known as Audi Revolut F1 team following a partnership with the global fintech company.</p> <p>Of more concern to drivers Nico H&uuml;lkenberg and Gabriel Bortoleto, as well as F1 project boss Mattia Binotto and team principal Jonathan Wheatley, is how the car will perform. Audi has taken on a herculean task in producing its own power unit as well as its chassis, and admits that it&rsquo;s likely to need five years to become a title contender.<a id="alpine"></a></p> <p><a class="button button--outline" href="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/audi-2026-f1-car-launch-new-livery-revealed/">2026 Audi F1 car launch</a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Alpine</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: January 23</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1475494" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-scaled.jpg" alt="Rear shot of Alpine F1 car leaving pit garage" width="2560" height="1440" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-200x113.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-818x460.jpg 818w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-946x532.jpg 946w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rear-shot-of-Alpine-F1-car-leaving-pit-garage-678x381.jpg 678w" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px"></p> <p>Alpine&rsquo;s livery launch is likely to be overshadowed by Ferrari&rsquo;s event which takes place on the same day. Will the result be different on track?</p> <p>After years in the doldrums Renault has pulled out as an F1 engine supplier, but its Alpine brand continues as a constructor now powered by Mercedes.</p> <p>If rumours prove correct and the power unit is the class of the field, then it could transform the fortunes of the team, assuming that it can build a capable chassis.<a id="cadillac"></a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <hr> <h3><strong>Cadillac</strong></h3> <h4 role="crosshead">Livery reveal date: February 15</h4> <p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1473036" src="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo.jpg" alt="Cadillac F1 team logo" width="1890" height="1063" srcset="https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo.jpg 1890w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-300x169.jpg 300w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-768x432.jpg 768w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-1600x900.jpg 1600w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-800x450.jpg 800w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-400x225.jpg 400w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-660x371.jpg 660w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-330x186.jpg 330w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-165x93.jpg 165w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-82x46.jpg 82w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-658x370.jpg 658w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-329x185.jpg 329w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-172x97.jpg 172w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-200x112.jpg 200w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-450x253.jpg 450w, https://uat.motorsportmagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Cadillac-F1-team-logo-818x460.jpg 818w" sizes="(max-width: 1890px) 100vw, 1890px"></p> <p>Cadillac plans to launch in a blaze of publicity, befitting Formula 1&rsquo;s newest team. It has bought a slot during Super Bowl halftime break to reveal the US outfit&rsquo;s livery.</p> <p>The team will be based in Indianapolis, with a satellite facility in Silverstone. It will use a Ferrari engine initially, until its own power unit is developed at General Motors&rsquo; motor sport base in North Carolina.</p> <p>Valtteri Bottas and Sergio Perez will drive for Cadillac in its first year, with Colton Herta as test driver &ndash; the American will run an F2 campaign to gain the necessary superlicence points to become eligible for F1.</p> ]]>
